UML:TaggedValue.value: The AIRM Constraints Model provides the AIRM Constraints which have an impact on the AIRM Information Model and/or the AIRM Consolidated Logical Data Model.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: AIRM Constraints Applicable to the CLDM

UML:TaggedValue.value: Each SignificantPoint with navaidSystem.name assigned shall-have navaidSystem.name exactly six characters long.
Each ReferenceLocation with significant point assigned shall-have type equal to SIGNIFICANT_POINT
Each ReferenceLocation with trafficDestination assigned shall-have type equal to AERODROME or SET_OF_AERODROMES
Each ReferenceLocation with aerodrome assigned shall-have type equal to AERODROME
Each ReferenceLocation with levelRange assigned shall-have type equal to AIRSPACE or SIGNIFICANT_POINT
Each ReferenceLocation with airspace assigned shall-have type equal to AIRSPACE
Each ReferenceLocation with aerodromeSet assigned shall-have type equal to SET_OF_AERODROMES
Each RunwayContamination with clearedWidth assigned shall-have Runway.clearedWidth lower than or equal to RunwayContamination.nominalWidth.
Each RunwayContamination with clearedLength assigned shall-have Runway.clearedLength lower than or equal-to RunwayContamination.nominalLength.
Each ILSGlidepath with frequency assigned shall-have frequency expressed in closed interval between 328.6 {MHZ} and 335.4 {MHZ}.
Each Aerodrome with locationIndicatorICAO assigned shall-have locationIndicatorICAO exactly four characters long of-type {CodeUpperAlphaType}.
Each VOR with frequency assigned shall-be expressed in multiple of 50 {KHZ}.
Each NDB with frequency assigned shall- have frequency in closed interval between 190 {KHZ} and 1750 {KHZ}.
Each Aerodrome with designatorIATA assigned shall-have designatorIATA exactly three characters long of-type {CodeUpperAlphaType}.
Each Localizer with frequency assigned shall- have frequency expressed in closed interval between 108.000 {MHZ} and 111.975 {MHZ}.
Each MarkerBeacon with frequency shall- have frequency equal to 75 {MHZ}.
Each Localizer with frequency.uom assigned shall- have uom of-type {MHZ}.
Each VOR with frequency assigned shall-have frequency in closed interval between 108.000 {MHZ} and 117.975 {MHZ}.
If the aircraft registration marking is used as AircraftIdentification, the ICAO designator of the aircraft operator and the flight number shall not be provided.
FlightPhase.crusingSpeed is plausible only when FlightPhase.type = CRUISE.
FlightPhase.crusingLevel is plausible only when FlightPhase.type = CRUISE.
The SSRCode.code shall be exactly a series of 4 octal number.
FlightPhase.crusingAltitude is plausible only when FlightPhase.type = CRUISE.
FlightPhase.cruiseClimbSpeed is plausible only when FlightPhase.type = CHANGE_OF_CRUISE_LEVEL.
Each RunwayVisualRange with rvrValueInterpretation provided shall have rvrValueInterpretation equal to 'ABOVE' or 'BELOW'.
